the communist party central committee met sunday 
to fix the agenda for an extraordinary session of the soviet 
parliament which is expected to annul the partys monopoly on 
power and elect a vastly more powerful president 
the meeting of the ruling partys policymaking body comes the 
same day the lithuanian parliament is expected to declare its 
republics independence from the soviet union 
during the closeddoor central committee meeting president 
mikhail s gorbachev could come under fire for lithuanias 
independence movement the republics communist party already broke 
with the national party in moscow in december 
the central committee convened at 10 am in the kremlin the 
official tass news agency said in a brief dispatch at the top of 
its agenda were preparations for the session of the congress of 
peoples deputies scheduled to convene monday tass said 
officials reportedly will consider ending party control of the 
management of almost every factory and institution in the country 
in february party leaders agreed to give up their monopoly on 
power and compete in a multiparty system but reformers say the 
change will be ineffective unless the party also abolishes its 
committees in plants farms army units courts police precincts 
and elsewhere 
sundays session will also consider a revamped set of party 
rules including the election of delegates to a party congress by 
the rank and file previously party leaders approved the 
delegates who in turn confirmed the leaders in a system that 
preserved the status quo 
the congress meeting that opens monday is expected to approve 
the partys proposal for a more powerful presidency despite 
growing objections from reformers and outlying republics that the 
plan would concentrate dictatorial power in gorbachevs hands 
the soviet news service interfax said the central committee will 
return to its session to nominate its candidate for president after 
the congress passes the appropriate constitutional amendments 
gorbachev is expected to be elected to the post probably during 
the coming week 
