an army of federal workers is about to try to 
make thousands of nearly invisible people part of america 
the occasion is the first census of the homeless 
often in sight if not always seen these people do not exist 
for purposes of federal aid and representation unless they can be 
counted 
how many are there where do they live what kind of help to 
they need 
to many of the homeless though being counted seems likely to 
make little difference in their lives 
i dont see nothing i stand to lose or gain said spencer 
cox a homeless new yorker its just useless whats the point 
a homeless man in stamford conn echoed coxs view what 
