they should admit as members they could also keep up to 50 percent 
of the party dues paid by members 
but gorbachev did not embrace demands by some communist 
reformers for abolishing city and regional party committees they 
customarily dominate local government authorities and grassroots 
party organizations alike 
gorbachev said the fate of communist parties in eastern europe 
showed the danger that arises when party organizations in cities 
and regions are dissolved 
significantly the soviet leader also failed to endorse 
