local party barons from imposing their slates 
gorbachev stressed that the party should be a union of 
likeminded communists he thus ruled out the possibility that 
factions would finally be admitted in party ranks in contrast to 
the practice laid down by soviet founder vladimir i lenin 
likewise the new rules would permit the creation of a 
federalized party with independent organizations in the soviet 
republics as some party reformers wanted gorbachev said 
but he said the republiclevel parties would be granted real 
autonomy by the rules and a new party program that will be 
submitted to the july congress for adoption 
radicals and reformers inside and outside the communist party 
say that even if it is put on the same legal footing with other 
groups the party will retain its dominant role in soviet life it 
does so through groups of communists organized in government 
agencies farms army units police precincts and virtually every 
other institution 
gorbachev repeated it was necessary for the july congress to 
endorse a new role for the party that would get it out of running 
daytoday soviet affairs but he said party organizations based at 
the workplace would remain 
he also staked out a special position in society for the 
communist party even if its legal status is altered as the 
ruling party politically responsible before the people and one 
that will not engage in trivial parliamentary games 
according to the interfax news agency of staterun radio moscow 
