the leipzig trade fair opened 
sunday providing the first major meeting ground for west german 
firms rushing to link with partners in east germany since the 
collapse of communist control 
the spring edition of the twiceyearly fair which focuses on 
industrial machines and electrical equipment comes at a time when 
both germanys are moving steadily toward de facto economic unity 
few cooperation agreements are expected to be signed however 
before the march 18 parliamentary elections in east germany 
small and middlesized western firms are especially prominent at 
the weeklong fair which east german economic minister christa 
luft dubbed a marketplace of new chances 
west german companies increased their presence by about 25 
percent over last year accounting for some 1000 of the shows 
9000 displays by manufacturers from 60 countries 
