with his countrys struggling firms have faith in us he said 
on the fringes of the fair adam opel ag the west german arm of 
us automaking giant general motors signed an agreement sunday to 
coproduce passenger cars in east germany with the automobilwerk 
eisenach company 
under the joint venture agreement both partners said they hope 
to produce 150000 opel cars yearly at the east german companys 
plant at eisenach near the west german border 
organizers expect half a million visitors in the fair halls 
where all available display space was occupied for the first time 
in years some applicants were put on a waiting list 
